description:
This Mother's Day, I've teamed up with Sekaya to put together something healthy, fun, and delicious (and pink!) for all the moms and mom figures. Because you all deserve a treat on Mother's Day and every day! And since the recipe is pink, consider it my endorsement for Leni in this upcoming election (I hope she wins!)
Vegan Pink Fettuccine Alredo
Ingredients:
500 grams fettuccine noodles
6 cloves of garlic, minced
3-5 tablespoons olive oil
2 cups coconut milk
1 cup soymilk (make sure it's unsweetened)
1 tablespoon flour
1 tablespoon mushroom broth powder (you can also use white miso paste)
1 teaspoon Sekaya pea protein
1 tablespoon Sekaya beets powder

For the shiitake bacon:
1/4 cup dried shiitake mushrooms
boiling water for soaking
3-5 tablespoons cooking oil
2 tablespoons brown sugar
1 tablespoon soy sauce
sprinkle of salt

Tofu feta 
1 1/2 cup firm tofu, crumbled
1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar
1 teaspoon salt
sprinkle of dried oregano
drizzle of olive oil

Basil for garnish

Bring a pot of heavily salted water to a rapid boil then add your noodles. Cook for 10-12 minutes then drain.

Heat a medium pan over medium heat and pour the olive oil. Cook the onion and garlic in oil for 5 minutes or until the onions have turned soft and slightly translucent.

In a bowl, combine the coconut milk, soymilk, flour, mushroom broth, Sekaya beets powder, and Sekaya pea protein. Whisk until well combined.

Pour the sauce into the sauteed garlic and onions and cook for 3 minutes or until the sauce has slightly thickened.

Add the pasta noodles and using tongs, mix thoroughly to coat the noodles.

To make the mushroom bacon:Soak the mushrooms in boiling water for 15 minutes or until they softened. Cut to strips.Heat a medium pan over medium heat and add the oil.Once the oil is hot, fry the mushrooms. Season with brown sugar, soy sauce, and salt. Once the sugar caramelizes, turn off the heat.

To make the tofu feta:In a bowl, mix all of the ingredients: tofu, apple cider vinegar, salt, oregano, and olive oil.

To assemble, place the fettuccine alfredo on a serving plate, top with mushroom bacon and tofu feta. Garnish with basil.

Kain na, let's eat!
